<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/323201-interesting-how-people-ripped-apart-the">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Interesting how people ripped apart "The Light Between Oceans" by M. L. Stedman for the main characters' keeping (and then eventually having to give back) a baby who washes ashore, and yet the people who just keep Nell (Ivory) are not vilified by reviewers. Granted, there is a lot more to "The Forgotten Garden" than just this aspect, but where is the outrage for Hugh and Lil? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
