<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/17458475-christy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1368071094i/17458475._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/17458475-christy">Christy</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Perhaps I was reading too deeply into it, but I believe that Hugh and Lil would have been part of Ivory/Nell's family anyway. Eliza had planned to go <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Perhaps I was reading too deeply into it, but I believe that Hugh and Lil would have been part of Ivory/Nell's family anyway. Eliza had planned to go to Maryborough because Mary's family was there. Not just her brother, but also her aunt Eleanor. When Ivory arrived at Hugh &amp; Lil's with no recollection of her name, they called her "Nell" after Lil's mother Eleanor. Of course, there could be dozens of women named Eleanor in the city, but I don't think the author would have mentioned both Eleanor's if they were not the same woman. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
